data.title: The Golden Bullet (1921 film)
data.meta_description: The Golden Bullet is a 1921 German silent adventure film directed by Robert Wuellner and starring Gertrude Welcker, Erich Kaiser-Titz and Otto Treptow. It premiered in Berlin on 24 March 1921.
